### Xcode / iOS ###
# Relay.xcodeproj and the generated Info.plist are produced by `xcodegen generate` from
# project.yml — see docs/07-implementation-plan.md and the CI workflow. Not checked in, so there's
# nothing to conflict/drift when project.yml changes.
Relay.xcodeproj/
Generated/

build/
DerivedData/
*.hmap
*.ipa
*.dSYM.zip
*.dSYM

## User settings
xcuserdata/

## Obj-C/Swift specific
*.moved-aside

## Swift Package Manager
.swiftpm/
.build/

## CocoaPods (not used, kept for safety if ever introduced)
Pods/

## Secrets — never commit these to a public repo
# The App Store Connect API key (.p8) is a live credential: it authorizes uploading builds and
# managing this developer account. It belongs outside the repo entirely (Codemagic stores its own
# copy); these patterns exist so an accidental drop into the working tree can't be committed.
# Same for signing certificates/profiles, which Codemagic manages via the API key anyway.
*.p8
*.p12
*.mobileprovision
*.cer
AuthKey_*

## Misc
.DS_Store
